  "text_preview": "\"table\" American Sign Language (ASL) ASL University ► American Sign Language: \"table\" The sign \"table\" simply shows a flat top. This sign can also mean \"desk.\" You might see \"DESK\" using the letter \"D\" on the dominant hand during this sign (initialization). TABLE: animation Here is an initialized version of the sign for \"table.\" Warning, this initialized version is not generally considered ASL. That may change in the future if more people start using it, (time will tell). I see it used here and there so I thought I'd include it just incase you come across it. If you mean \"table\" as in a chart or graph then see: SCHEDULE See: CHAIR You can learn American Sign Language (ASL) online at American Sign Language University ™ ASL resources by Lifeprint.com © Dr. William Vicars Want to help support"
